iveness and m=\r\nay not really *ensure* secretiveness. If everybody (especially the priest) =\r\nis sitting close to them, they may also hear it in spite of a the cloth cov=\r\nering them.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;When I did upanayanam to my son, we did the rituals in o=\r\npen air in our back yard. At the time of brahmopadesa muhurta, I took my so=\r\nn inside the pooja room where I did my sadhana. I did not allow anybody, in=\r\ncluding the priests, to come there. I taught the mantra to my son in an low=\r\n, but audible, voice. I repeated a few times, made him repeat it a few time=\r\ns, ensured his pronunciation was correct, and then both of us did a maalaa =\r\n(108 times meditation) with it silently. We then came back to the backyard =\r\nand the rituals continued.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;One more thing on muhurta: If you got a m=\r\nuhurta from an astrologer you trust and want to follow it, please ensure th=\r\nat\n Gayatri mantra is taught at that muhurta. THAT is the main event. Some =\r\npriests put a paste made of cumin seeds and jaggery on the young man&#39;s head=\r\n at the muhurta time. That is irrelevant and brahmopadesa is the main thing=\r\n.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;* * *&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Though we did a detailed ritual for my son&#39;s upanayan=\r\nam, my own upanayanam was a very simple affair. Though my father is an orth=\r\nodox braahmana following a very simple and austere lifestyle, he is unortho=\r\ndox in the matter of rituals. Above all, he fearlessly follows his convicti=\r\nons and does not engage in rituals that he does not consider meaningful. He=\r\n is also against following the letter of the rules and breaking the spirit.=\r\n For example, when he went to a griha pravesh (housewarming) ceremony once,=\r\n they were beating a cow to force it to climb stairs to enter the room. Peo=\r\nple bring a cow into the room at the time of housewarming, as they consider=\r\n a cow to symbolize Lakshmi and some steps in the ritual require a cow\n in =\r\nthe room. As the cow was not happy to climb stairs, they resorted to violen=\r\nce to force it. My father was sad to see the suffering of the cow and told =\r\nthem bluntly that they were doing adharma and there was no point in getting=\r\n a cow in the room like that. But my father puts more value on the spirit o=\r\nf the rules rather than the letter and does not hesitate to speak his mind =\r\nin front of anybody.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;For my upanayanam, he took me to Lord Venkatesw=\r\nara temple in Tirupati/Tirumala, which is his favorite temple. At the time =\r\nof muhurta, we were on the hill near the temple. He spent a few hours doing=\r\n his japam with various stotras and I also did japam with several stotras. =\r\nWhen the muhurta came, he simply taught me Gayatri mantra and that was it. =\r\nNo rituals of any kind were performed, except for japam for a few hours.&lt;BR=\r\n&gt;&lt;BR&gt;In my opinion, such a simple approach is also perfectly fine. The key =\r\npoints are that the person giving mantra should have done some\n sadhana, bo=\r\nth of them should be in a good and relaxed mood at the time and environment=\r\n should be peaceful, and, the person receiving mantra should do a lot of sa=\r\ndhana with it later on.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;If a businessman opens an account in his son=\r\n&#39;s name for a new business venture by the young man, what matters is how mu=\r\nch money father gave and how well the son used the money, how he ran the ne=\r\nw business and how he grew the money. How big a party was held, how many pe=\r\nople came and what activities they engaged in is irrelevant in the long run=\r\n.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;* * *&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;My purpose is not to discourage elaborate rituals. Do=\r\n them if there is social pressure to do so or you find them interesting. Bu=\r\nt, atleast ensure that mantropadesa happens peacefully and correctly. More =\r\nimportantly, ensure that the young man does some sadhana with Gayatri mantr=\r\na everyday, after upanayanam.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Also, it is perfectly acceptable (and =\r\nbeneficial) to initiate the young person into homam\n after upanayanam is do=\r\nne. On the same day or a few days later, one can teach a simple version of =\r\nGanapathi homam and let the young person perform it by oneself during weeke=\r\nnds or so. One can start off with the super-short procedure and slowly add =\r\nthings. Doing Gayatri mantra everyday and homam now and then will accelerat=\r\ne the spiritual evolution of the young person.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Best regards,&lt;BR&gt;Nara=\r\nsimha&lt;BR&gt;------------ --------- --------- --------- --------- --------- -&lt;B=\r\nR&gt;Free Jyotish Software, Free Jyotish Lessons, Jyotish Writings,&lt;BR&gt;&quot;Do It =\r\nYourself&quot; ritual manuals for short Homam and Pitri Tarpana:&lt;BR&gt;&lt;A href=3D&quot;h=\r\nttp://www.vedicastrologer.org/&quot; rel=3Dnofollow target=3D_blank&gt;http://www.V=\r\nedicAst rologer.org&lt;/A&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Films that make a difference: &lt;A href=3D&quot;http://=\r\nsaraswatifilms.org/&quot; rel=3Dnofollow target=3D_blank&gt;http://SaraswatiFil ms.=\r\norg&lt;/A&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Spirituality: &lt;A href=3D&quot;http://groups.yahoo.com/group/vedic-wis=\r\ndom&quot; rel=3Dnofollow target=3D_blank&gt;http://groups. yahoo.com/\n group/vedic-=\r\n wisdom&lt;/A&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Jyotish writings: &lt;A href=3D&quot;http://groups.yahoo.com/group/J=\r\nyotishWritings&quot; rel=3Dnofollow target=3D_blank&gt;http://groups. yahoo.com/ gr=\r\noup/JyotishWri tings&lt;/A&gt;&lt;BR&gt;------------ --------- --------- --------- ----=\r\n----- --------- -&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;---- Sunitha &lt;&lt;A href=3D&quot;http://in.mc955.mail.y=\r\nahoo.com/mc/compose?to=3Dsunitha_macherla%40yahoo.com&quot; rel=3Dnofollow targe=\r\nt=3D_blank&gt;sunitha_macherla@ yahoo.com&lt;/A&gt;&gt; wrote: &lt;BR&gt;&gt; Namaskaram N=\r\narasimha garu, Can the homam performed during upanayanam be done using only=\r\n coconuts and nuts? Do the samidhalu that priests use serve any specific pu=\r\nrpose of the ritual? What part(s) of Upanayanam ritual (or there after) sho=\r\nuld one not miss or be aware of? I want my son and us to be aware of the pr=\r\nocess rather than blindly doing what is asked of us. &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &lt;BR&gt;&gt; Your=\r\n response in the subject is much much appreciated. &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &lt;BR&gt;&gt; Thanks=\r\n in advance,&lt;BR&gt;&gt;\n -Sunitha&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&lt;/TD&gt;&lt;=\r\n/TR&gt;&lt;/TBODY&gt;&lt;/TABLE&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;&lt;b=\r\nr&gt;\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n      \r\n--0-1109812525-1276237786=:35525--\r\n\n"}}